        Automotive suppliers use corrugated sheets for heavy parts protection and component organization. The strength of A-flute sheets handles weight while preventing vibration damage during long shipments.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">Food and Beverage</h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Food producers use corrugated sheets for product separation, moisture protection, and structural support in heavy boxes of canned or bottled goods. The moisture resistance of quality corrugated sheets prevents contamination.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">E-Commerce and Retail</h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Online retailers use corrugated sheets to protect diverse products from books to cosmetics, ensuring safe delivery and positive unboxing experiences that encourage repeat purchases and positive reviews.
      </p>
    </section>

